## 🎯 Objective
To assess the security posture of the **OWASP Juice Shop** application by discovering vulnerabilities like:
- SQL Injection
- Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
- Broken Authentication
- Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)
- Sensitive Data Exposure

---

## 🛠️ Tools Used
- 🔸 OWASP Juice Shop
- 🔸 Burp Suite (Community Edition)
- 🔸 OWASP ZAP
- 🔸 SQLMap
- 🔸 Kali Linux (Optional)
- 🔸 Google Docs (for report compilation)

---

## ✅ Vulnerabilities Identified

| #  | Vulnerability             | OWASP Category            | Risk Level | Tool Used            |
|----|---------------------------|---------------------------|------------|----------------------|
| 1  | SQL Injection             | A01 – Injection            | High       | SQLMap, Burp Suite   |
| 2  | Cross-Site Scripting      | A07 – XSS                  | Medium     | OWASP ZAP, Burp      |
| 3  | Broken Authentication     | A02 – Broken Auth          | High       | Manual               |
| 4  | Cross-Site Request Forgery| A05 – Broken Access Control| Medium     | Burp Suite           |
| 5  | Sensitive Data Exposure   | A02 – Crypto Failures      | Medium     | Manual               |

---

